nds our understanding of Mediterranean politics, European perceptions of the Ottomans, and Ottoman interest in mapping and print. The envoy to the Sultan represented the aspirations of the Florentine state, which chose not to bestow some other highly valued good, such as the city's renowned textiles, but instead the best example of what Florentine visual, material, and intellectual culture had to offer.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 08. Jul 2019) 0aCartographyzItalyzFlorencexHistoryy15th century. 0aCartographyzTurkeyzIstanbulxHistoryy15th century. 7aHISTORY / Renaissance.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2013z9783110317350oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE HISTORY, POLITICAL SCIENCE, SOCIOLOGY  2013z978311031712108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET GESCHICHTE, POLITIKWISS., SOZIOLOGIE  2013z9783110317114oZDB-23-DPS08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP Complete eBook Package 2011-2014z978311037488908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook Package 2013z978311037490208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311044220508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014z978311045951708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2015z978311066256640uhttps://doi.org/10.4159/harvard.9780674068070423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780674068070.jpg  a978-3-11-031712-1  E-BOOK PACKAGE HISTORY, POLITICAL SCIENCE, SOCIOLOGY  2013b2013  a978-3-11-037488-9  HUP Complete eBook Package 2011-2014  a978-3-11-037490-2  HUP eBook Package 2013b2013  a978-3-11-044220-5  HUP eBook Package Backlist 2005-2013c2000d2013  a978-3